{"title":"C. Sequence","contestId":"13","problemIndex":"C","timeLimit":"1 second","memLimit":"64 megabytes","inputFormat":"standard input","outputFormat":"standard output","problemHtml":"<p>Little Petya likes to play very much. And most of all he likes to play the following game:</p><p>He is given a sequence of <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>N</i></span> integer numbers. At each step it is allowed to increase the value of any number by <span class=\"tex-span\">1</span> or to decrease it by <span class=\"tex-span\">1</span>. The goal of the game is to make the sequence non-decreasing with the smallest number of steps. Petya is not good at math, so he asks for your help.</p><p>The sequence <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i></span> is called non-decreasing if <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">2</sub>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;...&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>N</i></sub></span> holds, where <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>N</i></span> is the length of the sequence.</p>","inSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Input</div><p>The first line of the input contains single integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>N</i></span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">1&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>N</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;5000</span>) &#x2014; the length of the initial sequence. The following <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>N</i></span> lines contain one integer each &#x2014; elements of the sequence. These numbers do not exceed <span class=\"tex-span\">10<sup class=\"upper-index\">9</sup></span> by absolute value.</p>","outSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Output</div><p>Output one integer &#x2014; minimum number of steps required to achieve the goal.</p>","noteHtml":null,"sampleTestcases":[{"id":1613681330469,"input":"5\n3 2 -1 2 11\n","output":"4\n"},{"id":1613681330470,"input":"5\n2 1 1 1 1\n","output":"1\n"}],"submitUrl":"https://codeforces.com/contest/13/submit","language"